---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Container from '../components/ui/Container.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Start Here | Old Dog, New Flex" 
  description={`If you're new here, welcome. Old Dog, New Flex exists because I reached a point in my career where I stopped asking "What's next?" and started asking "What lasts?"`}
  heroImage="/images/old-dog-drawing-map.webp" 
  heroAlt="An elderly man with a long white beard and flowing hair, wearing bright, retro-futuristic clothes including an orange and pink jacket, neon sunglasses, large headphones sitting at a table in a coffee shop with a couple other people drawing a map on a piece of notebook paper.">

  <div class="hero-image hidden md:block md:absolute md:left-20 md:w-2/3 lg:w-1/3 md:top-[140px]">
    <p class="text-5xl font-extrabold text-left text-blue" style="text-shadow: 4px 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);">
      Start Here
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- One-paragraph orientation -->
  <section class="pt-16 pb-10">
    <Container size="sm">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue mb-6">Start Here</h1>
      <p class="text-xl">
        You've already seen what this site is about. This page skips the intro and gets you to
        the right first post — based on what actually brought you here.
      </p>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <!-- Self-select reading paths -->
  <section class="py-10 border-t border-surface1">
    <Container size="md">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8 text-subtext0 uppercase tracking-wide text-sm">Pick your path</h2>

      <!-- Path 1 -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue mb-2">
          If AI is changing how you work — and you're not sure whether to trust it
        </h3>
        <p class="text-subtext0 mb-5">
          These are for engineers who use AI tools daily but feel something off about how they're being used.
          Not AI skepticism — AI judgment.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <a href="/learn/ai-is-fast-production-is-fragile" class="block p-5 rounded-lg bg-surface0 border border-surface1 hover:border-mauve/50 transition-colors group">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-text group-hover:text-blue transition-colors">AI Is Fast, Production Is Fragile</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-subtext0 mt-1">Why speed without oversight creates the exact kind of debt that experience was supposed to prevent.</p>
              </div>
              <span class="text-subtext0 group-hover:text-blue transition-colors shrink-0 mt-1">→</span>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href="/learn/responsible-ai-adult-pov" class="block p-5 rounded-lg bg-surface0 border border-surface1 hover:border-mauve/50 transition-colors group">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-text group-hover:text-blue transition-colors">What It Means to Be a Responsible AI Adult</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-subtext0 mt-1">The framework I use for deciding when AI earns autonomy in my workflow — and when it doesn't.</p>
              </div>
              <span class="text-subtext0 group-hover:text-blue transition-colors shrink-0 mt-1">→</span>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Path 2 -->
      <div class="mb-12 pt-10 border-t border-surface1">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue mb-2">
          If you've been at this for a while and something isn't working anymore
        </h3>
        <p class="text-subtext0 mb-5">
          These are for experienced engineers who feel the gap between what they know and how they work.
          Burnout, identity shifts, figuring out where experience fits in the current moment.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <a href="/journey/burnout-wasnt-the-end" class="block p-5 rounded-lg bg-surface0 border border-surface1 hover:border-mauve/50 transition-colors group">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-text group-hover:text-blue transition-colors">Burnout Wasn't the End — It's Where My New Flex Began</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-subtext0 mt-1">The post that started all of this. What I learned by actually stopping, and why I came back differently.</p>
              </div>
              <span class="text-subtext0 group-hover:text-blue transition-colors shrink-0 mt-1">→</span>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href="/journey/stop-coding-start-supervising" class="block p-5 rounded-lg bg-surface0 border border-surface1 hover:border-mauve/50 transition-colors group">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-text group-hover:text-blue transition-colors">Stop Coding, Start Supervising</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-subtext0 mt-1">On making the shift from doing everything yourself to knowing what's worth directing — and what isn't.</p>
              </div>
              <span class="text-subtext0 group-hover:text-blue transition-colors shrink-0 mt-1">→</span>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Path 3 -->
      <div class="mb-10 pt-10 border-t border-surface1">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue mb-2">
          If you're not sure what this site is or whether it's for you
        </h3>
        <p class="text-subtext0 mb-5">
          These explain the thinking behind why this exists and what "learning" means in this context.
          Start here if you want to know what you're signing up for before diving in.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <a href="/learn/why-old-dog-new-flex-exists" class="block p-5 rounded-lg bg-surface0 border border-surface1 hover:border-mauve/50 transition-colors group">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-text group-hover:text-blue transition-colors">Why Old Dog, New Flex Exists</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-subtext0 mt-1">The honest origin story. Not a brand exercise — a career reckoning that turned into a writing habit.</p>
              </div>
              <span class="text-subtext0 group-hover:text-blue transition-colors shrink-0 mt-1">→</span>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href="/learn/what-i-mean-by-learning-and-what-i-dont" class="block p-5 rounded-lg bg-surface0 border border-surface1 hover:border-mauve/50 transition-colors group">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-text group-hover:text-blue transition-colors">What I Mean by Learning — and What I Don't</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-subtext0 mt-1">How I distinguish chasing novelty from actually building understanding. The filter I use before writing anything.</p>
              </div>
              <span class="text-subtext0 group-hover:text-blue transition-colors shrink-0 mt-1">→</span>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <!-- Lightweight closing CTA -->
  <section class="py-14 border-t border-surface1">
    <Container size="sm">
      <p class="text-xl mb-6">
        Not sure which path is yours? Start anywhere. The writing is self-contained —
        you don't need to read in order.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/learn" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-surface0 border border-surface1 hover:border-mauve/50 text-text transition-colors">
          Browse Learn →
        </a>
        <a href="/journey" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-surface0 border border-surface1 hover:border-mauve/50 text-text transition-colors">
          Browse Journey →
        </a>
        <a href="/about" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-surface0 border border-surface1 hover:border-mauve/50 text-text transition-colors">
          About this site →
        </a>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
